article.headline: Murray St. 75, Tennessee St. 71
article.story: MURRAY, Ky. -- Isacc Miles' two free throws in the game's final seconds lifted Murray State over Tennessee State 75-71 on Thursday night. Miles and Ivan Aska were the leading scorers for the Racers (7-7, 2-2 Ohio Valley Conference) with 17 points apiece. Jerrell Houston led the Tigers (5-10, 3-2) with 18 points and 12 rebounds. Murray State got a three points apiece from Tyler Holloway and Aska during a 10-0 run late in the first half, helping Murray State to a 35-31 halftime lead. After Gerald Robinson's basket and free throw brought the Tigers within 72-71 in the game's final minute, Miles hit one free throw with 20 seconds left and another with 5 seconds remaining to put the Racers ahead by three points. The Tigers turned the ball over on their final possession, and Aska hit a final free throw to seal the victory.
